properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued January 14 at 1:42PM MST until January 15 at 2:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...ANOTHER ROUND OF STRONG GUSTY WINDS POSSIBLE TONIGHT THROUGH
EARLY WEDNESDAY MORNING...

The National Weather Service in Cheyenne has issued a High Wind
Watch, which is in effect from 9 PM MST this evening through
Wednesday afternoon.

* TIMING...Late this evening through early Wednesday afternoon.

* WINDS...West to northwest between 30 to 45 mph with occasional
gusts up to 65 mph.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Strong cross winds may
create dangerous travel conditions. There is a high blow-over
risk for light and high profile vehicles, including campers
and tractor trailers.

* ADDITIONAL IMPACTS...Snow showers are expected tonight in
addition to the gusty winds. This may create areas of blowing
and drifting snow. This combination may reduce visibilities
below 1 mile at times.
properties.instruction:
A High Wind Watch means there is the potential for a hazardous
high wind event. Sustained winds of at least 40 mph...or gusts of
58 mph or stronger may occur. Continue to monitor the latest
forecasts.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH IN EFFECT FROM 9 PM MST THIS EVENING THROUGH WEDNESDAY AFTERNOON
